## MongoDB CRUD

MongoDB stores documents as BSON (binary JSON) in collections. Every document has a unique `_id`.

```js
// Insert
db.users.insertOne({ name: 'Alice', age: 30, tags: ['admin'] });
db.users.insertMany([{ name: 'Bob' }, { name: 'Carol' }]);

// Query
db.users.find({ age: { $gt: 25 } });       // greater than
db.users.find({ tags: 'admin' });           // array contains
db.users.findOne({ name: 'Alice' });        // first match

// Update
db.users.updateOne({ name: 'Alice' }, { $set: { age: 31 }, $push: { tags: 'editor' } });
db.users.updateMany({ age: { $lt: 18 } }, { $set: { status: 'minor' } });

// Delete
db.users.deleteOne({ name: 'Bob' });
db.users.deleteMany({ status: 'inactive' });
```

## MongoDB Aggregation Pipeline

The aggregation pipeline transforms documents through sequential stages. Each stage passes its output as input to the next.

```js
// Sales analytics: revenue per category, top 3
db.orders.aggregate([
  { $match: { status: 'completed', date: { $gte: ISODate('2024-01-01') } } },
  { $unwind: '$items' },
  { $group: {
    _id: '$items.category',
    totalRevenue: { $sum: { $multiply: ['$items.price', '$items.qty'] } },
    orderCount: { $sum: 1 }
  }},
  { $sort: { totalRevenue: -1 } },
  { $limit: 3 },
  { $project: { _id: 0, category: '$_id', totalRevenue: 1, orderCount: 1 } }
]);
```

**Key stages:** `$match` (filter), `$group` (aggregate), `$sort`, `$limit`, `$project` (reshape), `$unwind` (flatten arrays), `$lookup` (JOIN), `$addFields`.

## MongoDB Indexing

Indexes are the primary tool for query performance. Without an index, MongoDB does a collection scan (COLLSCAN) — O(n).

```js
// Single field index
db.users.createIndex({ email: 1 });  // 1=asc, -1=desc

// Compound index — order matters: equality first, then sort, then range
db.orders.createIndex({ userId: 1, status: 1, createdAt: -1 });

// Text index for full-text search
db.articles.createIndex({ title: 'text', body: 'text' });
db.articles.find({ $text: { $search: 'mongodb indexing' } });

// Partial index — only index active users (smaller, faster)
db.users.createIndex({ email: 1 }, { partialFilterExpression: { isActive: true } });

// Explain: IXSCAN = index used, COLLSCAN = full scan (bad)
db.orders.find({ userId: 'u1' }).explain('executionStats');
```

## NoSQL Data Modeling

The core principle: **model data the way your application queries it**, not the way the real world looks.

**Embedding (denormalized):** Nest related data inside the parent document.
```js
// Embed comments inside post — fetched together always
{
  _id: 'post1',
  title: 'NoSQL Guide',
  author: { _id: 'u1', name: 'Alice' },  // embed author snapshot
  comments: [
    { userId: 'u2', text: 'Great!', date: ISODate() }
  ]
}
```

**Referencing (normalized):** Store foreign keys and join at query time.
```js
// Reference — author can change without updating all posts
{ _id: 'post1', title: 'NoSQL Guide', authorId: 'u1' }
{ _id: 'u1', name: 'Alice', email: 'a@b.com' }
// Requires two queries or $lookup
```

**Rules:** Embed when data is accessed together, rarely changes, array is bounded. Reference when data is shared across entities, accessed independently, or array is unbounded.
